modules.description: Prints OCaml values in a readable format using specialized functions for primitive types and structured data. Handles unit, boolean, integer, floating-point, and string values, along with options, lists, and tuples. Generates formatted output suitable for debugging or logging.

Prints the internal structure of documents and their rendered form with adjusted line breaks. Operates on document structures representing formatted text. Useful for visualizing layout transformations during debugging.

Provides functions to format and display OCaml values in a human-readable layout, supporting nested structures and controlled line breaks. Works with arbitrary data types through a flexible document abstraction that combines text, spacing, and grouping. Used to generate readable output for debugging, logging, or exporting structured data in a consistent format.

Provides functions to serialize OCaml values and document structures into human-readable formats. Handles primitive types, collections, and document layouts, with support for custom formatting and line break adjustments. Converts values like integers, lists, and tuples into readable strings, and renders document structures with explicit line breaks. Enables debugging by displaying both abstract syntax and rendered output.
